summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.

This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2002 to 2008.
Conversely, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2015 to 2019.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2008 to 2012.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2012 to 2015.
Conversely, the next significant trend is moderately constant which exists from 1999 to 2002.
